<h2><a name="temporalbinding"></a>Temporal binding of features in human vision</h2>
<p>The real world is a dynamic and ever-changing visual environment where stimuli compete for our attention not only in space, but also in time. Correctly combining visual features that are continuously changing over time represents another dimension of the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Binding_problem" target="_blank">binding problem</a> that the brain must solve, as the example below shows.</p>
