<h2><a name="changeblindness"></a>The power of attention - Change Blindness</h2>
<p>It is our ability to selectively pay attention to specific stimuli that allows us to 'glue' features together into distinct mental representations.As the phenomenon of <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Change_blindness" target="_blank">change blindness</a> shown below demonstrates, selective attention means that we actually consciously 'see' only a small part of our visual worlds, and are 'blind' to the rest.</p>
